Value.English: Remember Azimuth For Dry Run
Remember (store) an Azimuth value in the memory of the receiving Unit under the specified Note Type, for the duration of the current Dry Run.
Note Type
Determines the type of Note to remember.
Value
The value to be remembered.

Recall Azimuth For Dry Run

Returns an Azimuth value that was previousely remembered in the specified Unit as a Dry Run Note (see RememberAzimuthForDryRun Doctrinal Command). If the specified NoteType was not remembered in the specified Unit as a Dry Run Note - Null Azimuth is returned.
Unit
The Unit whose memory is checked.
Recall Boolean For Dry Run
